         <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">

<ab><lb n="1"/><persName nymRef="#Ἄτταλος  Περείτου  Δημητρίου  Ἄνδρων" type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἄτταλος">Ἄτταλος</name>  <persName type="attested"><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Περείτας">Περείτου</name></persName> <w lemma="ὁ">τοῦ</w> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Δημήτριος">Δημητρίου</name></persName></persName>  <name nymRef="#Ἄνδρων">Ἄνδρων</name></persName> <w lemma="ὁ">τῇ</w> <w lemma="πατρίς">πα<lb n="2" break="no"/> τρίδι</w> <w lemma="ἐκ">ἐκ</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῶν</w> <w lemma="ἴδιος">ἰδίων</w> <w lemma="οὗτος">τοῦτον</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τὸν</w> <w lemma="κίων">κείονα</w> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι">ἀνέθηκεν</w><lb n="3"/> <w lemma="ὗς">σῦν</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῷ</w> <w lemma="σπειροκέφαλον">σπειροκεφάλῳ</w></ab>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>Attalos Andron son of Peritas the son of Demetrius dedicated this column with its capital for his homeland at his own expense.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>One of the column base dedications from west portico of the East Court of the Hadrianic Baths. From north section: <ref type="inscription" n="1114" target="050206.xml"/> (MiItal 8 i and ii), <ref type="inscription" n="1116" target="050201.xml"/> (=Haussoullier1), <ref type="iAph" target=".xml"/> (=Boulanger A 73, no.11); from the south section <ref type="iAph" target=".xml"/> (=Boulanger B, 21 no.28), ?<ref type="inscription" n="1117" target="050202.xml"/> (=Museum 154), ?<ref type="iAph" target=".xml"/> (=Museum 158); cf also <ref type="iAph" target=".xml"/> (=68.272)</p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography">
            <p>Published from Boulanger's notes by <bibl n="haussoullier1920">Haussoullier, <title level="j">RPh</title> 44, 1920, <citedRange>74</citedRange>
               </bibl>, whence <bibl n="PHI">
                  <author>McCabe</author>
                  <title level="m">PHI Aphrodisias</title>
                  <citedRange n="257012">133</citedRange>
               </bibl>.</p>
         </div>
